{title: Burnt Fingers}
{artist: Ray Price}
{composer: Written by Robert Wright and George Forrest}

[C]When a [G7]man plays with fire he gets [C]burnt fingers
When he's a [G7]playin' with desire he gets [C]burnt fingers
When a man starts to [E7]trifle and leaves [F]his true love all alone
He'll [D7]break her heart and [G7]break his
When a [C]man gets burnt [E7]fingers he gets the [F]deepest kind of [D7]blues
When a [G7]man plays with fire he's bound to [C]lose